==English==
'''Muskellunge''' or '''muskie''' (''Esox masquinongy'') are large, relatively rare freshwater [[fish]] of [[North America]]. They are the largest member of the [[esox|pike]] family, [[Esocidae]]. Their native range includes the [[St. Lawrence River]], [[Great Lakes (North America)|Great Lakes]], [[Hudson Bay]] and [[Mississippi River]] basins.

